Title: NBA 2K19 LeBron James Reveal Trailer - NBA 2K 20th Anniversary Edition
Comment:
Awful junk of a trailer. Classic LeChoke trying to push through his agenda, the same thing he's been doing subliminally and through his media bots for years. He has the temerity to put GOAT on the poster after pretty much every basketball fan an expert has had enough of that bullshit after this finals against the GSW. 

Now, let's see what 2k has come up with. Are we going to be able to recreate key moments from his career? For example, can we step into LeChoke's shoes and dial a phone and call Wade, Bosh and a bunch of elite shooters to save our legacy? How about a first-person view of that Ray Allen trey? Of course, we'll need to brick 3 shots prior to that, but well worth it, I mean the view of Ray Allen not choking like we did must be great. 
Also, which button do we press to run Kyrie out of town? How much VC is that brace and how do we say that excuse on the presser - on the mic or do we have to type?

I guess the key question is will Delonte West appear in some capacity? His penetration surely deserves at least a mention? 

Pathetic. LeChoke the quitter, the loser, the diva.
